===Rectal use===
Vaginal specula are also used for [[anus|anal]] surgery, although several other forms of anal specula exist.  One form, the [[Anoscopy|anoscope]], resembles a tube that has a removable [[bullet]]-shaped insert.  When the anoscope is inserted into the anus, the insert dilates the anus to the diameter of the tube.  The insert is then removed, leaving the tube to allow examination of the lower rectum and anus.  

This style of anal speculum is one of the oldest designs for surgical instruments still in use, with examples dating back many centuries. The [[sigmoidoscope]] can be further advanced into the lower intestinal tract and requires an endoscopic set-up.

