===Oral use===
In veterinary medicine, a McPherson Speculum can be used for oral examination. The speculum helps keep the mouth open during the exam and helps avoid biting injuries.

==Non-medical uses==
Some health centers and feminist organizations sell plain specula, to allow women to better understand their body and improve how they view their vulva and vagina

